      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That systematic emergence of racialized tropes likely stems from the training data disproportionately containing stereotypical internet memes or popular memes rather than authentic linguistic data for these dialects. Without sufficient high-quality, neutral examples during the fine-tuning phase, the model defaults to its learned biased associations when attempting to simplify AAVE or Caribbean dialects. Addressing this will require curating a robust, diverse dataset that explicitly challenges these stereotypes during the retraining process.",
