      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing liability avoidance through the erasure of linguistic nuance often creates a new form of inauthenticity that can be just as damaging to brand reputation as the original trope issues. By suppressing distinct cultural markers to force conformity, you risk appearing insensitive or ignorant rather than professional. While risk management is valid, many consumers now value transparency and cultural respect over perfect safety, meaning this \"clean\" output may eventually be seen as lazily replacement.",
